#: ../iot/homeassistant/install_and_configure_esphome.rst:106
msgid "Edit the ``.yaml`` file."
msgstr ""

#: ../iot/homeassistant/install_and_configure_esphome.rst:108
msgid ""
"Click **EDIT** in the bottom right corner to go inside the ``.yaml`` "
"file, you will see the following default components."
msgstr ""

#: ../iot/homeassistant/install_and_configure_esphome.rst:113
msgid "``esphome``: Contains the name, platform, and board type that you set up."
msgstr ""

#: ../iot/homeassistant/install_and_configure_esphome.rst:114
msgid ""
"`logger <https://esphome.io/components/logger.html?highlight=logger>`_: "
"The logger component automatically logs all log messages through the "
"serial port and through MQTT topics."
msgstr ""

#: ../iot/homeassistant/install_and_configure_esphome.rst:115
msgid ""
"`api <https://esphome.io/components/api.html?highlight=api>`_: The "
"ESPHome native API is used to communicate with clients directly, with a "
"highly-optimized network protocol. Currently, only the ESPHome tool and "
"Home Assistant use this native API."
msgstr ""

#: ../iot/homeassistant/install_and_configure_esphome.rst:116
msgid ""
"`ota <https://esphome.io/components/ota.html?highlight=ota>`_: With the "
"OTA (Over The Air) update component you can upload your firmware binaries"
" to your node without having to use a USB cable for uploads."
msgstr ""

#: ../iot/homeassistant/install_and_configure_esphome.rst:117
msgid ""
"`wifi <https://esphome.io/components/wifi.html?highlight=wifi>`_: This "
"core ESPHome component sets up WiFi connections to access points for you."
" It needs to be in your configuration or otherwise ESPHome will fail in "
"the config validation stage."
msgstr ""

#: ../iot/homeassistant/install_and_configure_esphome.rst:118
msgid ""
"`captive_portal "
"<https://esphome.io/components/captive_portal.html?highlight=captive_portal>`_:"
" The captive portal component in ESPHome is a fallback mechanism for when"
" connecting to the configured WiFi fails. After 1 minute of unsuccessful "
"WiFi connection attempts, the ESP will start a WiFi hotspot (with the "
"credentials from your configuration)."
msgstr ""

